BT /F1 16 Tf 42 805 Td (Assignment 1 - PS12 - Optimal Planner) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 776 Td (Group ID: G108) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 755 Td (Team members: ARTHIKA G.; SRINEVEDA R S.; ASWATHY H.; AMIYA PALAI.; KUTAREKAR) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 744 Td (NISHCHAL AJAY.) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 42 723 Td (1. Problem Definition) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 698 Td (The problem is to plan a route for a delivery robot in a static 5 x 5 warehouse) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 687 Td (grid. The robot starts at S = \(0, 0\), must reach G = \(4, 4\), and must avoid blocked) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 676 Td (cells marked X. The allowed moves are Up, Down, Left, and Right. Diagonal movement) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 665 Td (is not allowed. Each valid move has cost 1.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 644 Td (The blocked cells in the supplied grid are \(0, 3\), \(1, 1\), \(1, 3\), \(2, 1\), \(3, 2\),) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 633 Td (and \(3, 3\). The search uses Local Beam Search with beam width k = 2.) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 42 612 Td (2. PEAS Definition) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 587 Td (Performance measure: Reach the goal from the start, avoid obstacles and invalid) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 576 Td (moves, minimize total path cost, and print a clear search trace with selected beam) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 565 Td (states and heuristic values.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 544 Td (Environment: A fully observable, deterministic, static 2D warehouse grid containing) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 533 Td (free cells, blocked cells, one start state, and one goal state.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 512 Td (Actuators: Move Up, Move Down, Move Left, and Move Right.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 491 Td (Sensors: The robot reads its current position, grid boundaries, blocked cells, start) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 480 Td (position, and goal position from the input grid.) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 42 459 Td (3. Heuristic And Cost Functions) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 434 Td (The heuristic function is Manhattan Distance:) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 413 Td (h\(n\) = |goal_row - current_row| + |goal_column - current_column|) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 392 Td (This heuristic is appropriate because the robot can move only horizontally or) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 381 Td (vertically. It gives the minimum number of moves needed to reach the goal in an) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 370 Td (obstacle-free grid.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 349 Td (The cost function assigns cost 1 to every valid move. Therefore:) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 328 Td (g\(n\) = number of moves from S to n) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 317 Td (total path cost = number of moves in the final route) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 296 Td (For the given grid, the Manhattan lower bound from S = \(0, 0\) to G = \(4, 4\) is 8.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 285 Td (The implemented search finds a route of cost 8, so the route is optimal for this) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 274 Td (grid.) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 42 253 Td (4. Algorithm Design) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 228 Td (The program implements Local Beam Search with k = 2. The initial beam contains only) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 217 Td (the start node. At every iteration, successors are generated from all states in the) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 206 Td (current beam using the move order Up, Down, Left, Right. Invalid successors are) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 195 Td (removed if they are outside the grid, blocked by X, or already present in the same) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 184 Td (path.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 163 Td (Duplicate states are removed by position. If the same position is reached through) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 152 Td (more than one path, the implementation keeps the best node using the deterministic) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 141 Td (order: lower heuristic, lower path cost, lower row index, lower column index, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 130 Td (finally lexicographic path order. The best k states are inserted into a bounded) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 119 Td (BeamFringe and become the next beam. The search stops when the goal is selected in) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 108 Td (the beam or when no valid successor remains.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 87 Td (For the given grid, the final path is:) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 66 Td (\(0, 0\) -> \(0, 1\) -> \(0, 2\) -> \(1, 2\) -> \(2, 2\) -> \(2, 3\) -> \(2, 4\) -> \(3, 4\)) Tj ET
