BT /F1 12 Tf 42 763 Td (5. Data Structures And Fringe Design) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 738 Td (SearchNode stores the current position, full path, path cost, and heuristic value.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 727 Td (IterationRecord stores the trace for each iteration: current beam, generated) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 716 Td (successors, duplicate-free successors, and selected beam states. BeamFringe is a) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 705 Td (bounded queue-like structure with capacity k. Its insert operation raises a clear) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 694 Td (error when the fringe is full, and its delete operation raises a clear error when) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 683 Td (the fringe is empty. This satisfies the required data-structure error handling.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 662 Td (The grid is stored as a two-dimensional list. Candidate states are sorted using) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 651 Td (Python's stable sorting, and duplicates are removed using a dictionary keyed by grid) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 640 Td (position.) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 42 619 Td (6. Complexity Analysis) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 594 Td (Let k be the beam width, b be the branching factor, and d be the depth of the) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 583 Td (solution. In this problem, b <= 4 because only four actions are possible. At each) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 572 Td (level, at most k states are expanded and up to k*b successors are generated. The) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 561 Td (successors are sorted to select the best k states.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 540 Td (Time complexity: O\(d * k * b log\(k*b\)\).) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 519 Td (Space complexity: O\(k * d\), because each selected beam node stores its path. With) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 508 Td (fixed k = 2 and b <= 4, the search is memory efficient compared with exhaustive) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 497 Td (search.) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 42 476 Td (7. Alternate Modeling Approach) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 451 Td (An alternate way to model the problem is as a graph search problem solved using A*) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 440 Td (Search. Each free grid cell becomes a node, and edges connect valid four-directional) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 429 Td (neighbors with cost 1. A* uses f\(n\) = g\(n\) + h\(n\), where g\(n\) is the path cost so) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 418 Td (far and h\(n\) is Manhattan Distance. With this admissible heuristic, A* can guarantee) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 407 Td (an optimal path if one exists, but it may require more memory because it maintains) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 396 Td (larger open and closed lists. Local Beam Search uses less memory by retaining only k) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 385 Td (promising states at each level, but it can prune alternatives aggressively in harder) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 374 Td (grids.) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 42 353 Td (8. Implementation Notes) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 328 Td (The Python file is modular and reads the grid from inputPS12.txt, so the grid is not) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 317 Td (hardcoded. The output trace is written to outputPS12.txt and printed to the console.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 306 Td (Basic error handling is included for invalid input files, wrong dimensions, missing) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 295 Td (start or goal states, invalid grid symbols, invalid k values, full fringe insertion,) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 42 284 Td (and empty fringe deletion.) Tj ET
